{% if include.domain == "computers" %}

*[HW]: Hardware
*[SW]: Software

*[CPU]: The main processor ("Central Processing Unit")
*[C]: Number of CPU cores
*[HT]: Number of CPU threads
*[TDP]: Thermal Design Power

*[RAM]: The main memory ("Random-Access Memory")
*[DRAM]: Dynamic RAM ("Random-Access Memory")
*[DDR]: Double Data Rate Synchronous Dynamic Random-Access Memory (SDRAM)

*[HDD]: Hard Disk Drive
*[SSD]: Solid-State Drive
*[SATA]: Serial ATA interface
*[SAS]: Serial Attached SCSI ("Small Computer System Interface")
*[SCSI]: Peripheral devices standard ("Small Computer System Interface")
*[HBA]: Host Bus Adapter
*[RAID]: Redundant Array of Independent Disks
*[NVME]: m.2 SSD form factor ("Non-Volatile Memory (NVM) Express")
*[NGFF]: m.2 SSD form factor ("Next Generation Form Factor")
*[WD]: "Western Digital" disk manufacturer
*[TRIM]: The SSD "garbage collection" support technology

*[CD]: Compact Disk
*[DVD]: Digital Versatile Disk
*[BR]: Blu-Ray Disk
*[ISO]: Disc image standard (short for ISO-9660)

*[USB]: Computer connector interface ("Universal Serial Bus")

*[OHCI]: USB controller standard ("Open Host Controller Interface")
*[UHCI]: USB controller standard ("Universal Host Controller Interface")
*[EHCI]: USB 2.0 high speed controller standard ("Enhanced Host Controller Interface")
*[xHCI]: USB 3.0+ controller standard ("Extensible Host Controller Interface")
*[VHCI]: Virtualized USB controller standard ("Virtual Host Controller Interface")
*[AHCI]: Serial-ARA controller standard ("Advanced Host Controller Interface")

*[MB]: Motherboard
*[ATX]: Computer form factor ("Advanced Technology eXtended")
*[ITX]: Computer form factor ("Information Technology eXtended")
*[PCI]: Computer peripheral bus standard ("Peripheral Component Interconnect")
*[PCIe]: PCI-Express ("Peripheral Component Interconnect")
*[SFF]: Small Form Factor

*[LAN]: Local Area Network
*[NIC]: Network card ("Network Interface Controller")

*[TCP]: Network transport protocol ("Transmission Control Protocol")
*[UDP]: Network transport protocol ("User Datagram Protocol")
*[IP]: Network transport protocol ("Internet Protocol")
*[DHCP]: Network management protocol ("Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol")
*[DNS]: Hierarchical computer naming system ("Domain Name System")
*[HTTP]: Network application protocol ("Hypertext Transfer Protocol")
*[HTTPS]: Network application protocol ("Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure")
*[FTP]: Network application protocol ("File Transfer Protocol")
*[WINS]: Network name resolution protocol ("Windows Internet Naming Service")

*[PWM]: Pulse-Width Modulation
*[DC]: Direct Current
*[RPM]: Revolutions Per Minute

*[PSU]: Power Supply Unit
*[SFX]: Small Form Factor (SFF) power supply standard

*[DAS]: Direct Attached Storage
*[NAS]: Network Attached Storage
*[SAN]: Storage Area Network

*[OS]: Operating System
*[LTS]: Long Term Support
*[GUI]: Graphical User Interface
*[UAC]: Windows account protection technology ("User Account Control")

*[SSH]: Secure SHell network communication protocol

*[Ext]: Standard Linux File System
*[XFS]: Modern Linux Journaling File System
*[CoW]: Copy on Write
*[BtrFS]: Linux CoW File System
*[ZFS]: Sun Microsystems File System (initially Solaris-only)
*[ZoL]: ZFS on Linux

*[VM]: Virtual Machine

{% endif %}
